description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting and challenging time within the QEH Medicine Division within Lewisham and Greenwich Healthcare trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are pleased to announce a post of specialist medicine matron for Queen Elizabeth Hospital to lead and manage our progressive team, working within our Cardiology, Cardiac Catheter Lab, Neurology, Rheumatology, Dermatology, Respiratory and Diabetes and Endocrinology..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Matron you will provide clinical, professional and line management to the nursing teams. You will demonstrate effective leadership and continually monitor and maintain clinical standards. You will work alongside the Senior nursing team, Medical team, clinical reference groups within the Trust and report directly to the Head of Nursing for Specialist Medicine.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The matron’s role is to ensure the quality and safety of all patients within the division and to ensure that a high standard of clinical care is delivered by the entire multidisciplinary team at all times. Candidate will need to be passionate about ensuring that the work force you lead delivers the highest standards of care to all patients and ensuring the patient experience is positive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer a friendly supportive environment that values individuals in their personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any further information or would like to arrange an informal visit. Please contact Head of Nursing Tracey Toomey via email traceytoomey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTracey ToomeyJob titleHead of NursingEmail addresstraceytoomey@nhs.netTelephone number07342066993&lt;/p&gt;
